item.title: QuickBooks Online Accountant and PowerBI Analyst - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a skilled QuickBooks Online Accountant and PowerBI Analyst to join our team. As an analyst, you will be responsible for managing and analyzing financial data using QuickBooks Online and creating insightful reports using PowerBI. The ideal candidate should have a strong understanding of accounting principles, be proficient in QuickBooks Online, and have experience in data analysis and visualization using PowerBI. This role requires attention to detail, strong analytical skills, and the ability to communicate complex financial information effectively.

Responsibilities:
- Manage and maintain financial data on QuickBooks Online
- Analyze financial data and generate reports using PowerBI
- Identify trends and patterns in financial data
- Collaborate with the finance team to develop financial forecasts and budgets

Requirements:
- Proven experience as a QuickBooks Online Accountant
- Proficiency in PowerBI
- Strong understanding of accounting principles
- Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
- Ability to work independently and as part of a team
- Strong communication and presentation skills
- Attention to detail

This is a medium-sized project with a duration of 1 to 3 months. We are looking for an intermediate-level expert.

Budget: $10

item.title: Dynamics 365 On-Premise Environment Deployment - Upwork
item.description:
**Job Description:**

We are seeking an experienced freelancer to assist in deploying two environments of Dynamics 365 On-Premise - one for production and the other for User Acceptance Testing (UAT). The ideal candidate will have a strong background in Microsoft Dynamics 365 and experience in setting up and configuring on-premise environments.

**Responsibilities:**

- Deploy two separate environments of Dynamics 365 On-Premise - one for production and the other for UAT.
- Configure and optimize the environments to meet our organization's specific requirements.
- Implement security measures and access controls as per industry best practices.
- Collaborate with internal stakeholders to gather requirements and ensure alignment with business objectives.
- Troubleshoot any issues that arise during the deployment process and provide timely resolutions.

**Requirements:**

- Proven experience in deploying Dynamics 365 On-Premise environments, including installation, configuration, and customization.
- In-depth knowledge of Microsoft Dynamics 365 architecture and components.
- Familiarity with SQL Server and database management principles.
- Strong understanding of security concepts and protocols related to Dynamics 365.
- Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
- Effective communication skills, with the ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams.
- Prior experience working as a freelancer or in a consulting capacity is preferred.
- Relevant certifications in Dynamics 365 or related technologies would be a plus.

**Duration and Compensation:**

- This is a freelance project with an estimated duration of 5 days.
- Compensation will be based on the scope of work and mutually agreed upon terms.

Category: Solution Architecture

item.title: ETL Developer (Pentaho) - Upwork
item.description:
ETL DEVELOPER
Experience level: 5- 7 Years with Pentaho
Role overview:
• Focused on providing customer value by following delivery best practices to deliver and
supporting quality artefacts
• Implement data flows to connect operational systems, data for analytics and business
intelligence (BI) systems
• Document source-to-target mappings
• Re-engineer manual data flows to enable scaling and repeatable use
• Be responsible for the build of data-streaming systems
• Write ETL scripts and code to make sure the ETL process performs optimally
• Develop business intelligence reports that can be re-used
• Build accessible data for analysis
• Positive impact on wider team engineering practices
• Supports peers and juniors
Key Responsibilities:
• Communication skills (data). You can listen to the needs of technical and business
stakeholders and interpret them. You know how to manage stakeholder expectations. You are
flexible and capable of proactive and reactive communication. You know how to facilitate difficult
discussions within the team or with diverse senior stakeholders
• Data analysis and synthesis. You understand and can help teams apply a range of techniques
for data profiling. You can source system analysis from a complex single source. You can bring
multiple data sources together in a conformed model for analysis.
• Data development process. You can design, build and test data products that are complex or
large-scale. You know how to build teams to complete data integration services
• Data innovation. You can identify areas of innovation in data tools and techniques, and
recognise appropriate timing for adoption.
• Data integration design. You know how to select and implement the appropriate
technologies to deliver resilient, scalable and future-proofed data solutions.
• Data modelling. You understand the concepts and principles of data modelling and can
produce relevant data models. You know how to work across the business, recognising opportunities
for re-use and alignment between the data models in different teams. You can design the method to
categorise data model within the organisation.
• Metadata management. You can design an appropriate metadata repository and present
changes to existing metadata repositories. You understand a range of tools for storing and working
with metadata. You can provide oversight and advice to more inexperienced members of the team.
• Problem resolution (data). You can ensure that the most appropriate actions are taken to
resolve problems as they occur. You know how to coordinates teams to resolve problems and
implement solutions and preventative measures.
• Programming and build (data engineering). You know how to use agreed standards and tools
to design, code, test, correct and document moderate-to-complex programs and scripts from agreed
specifications and subsequent iterations. You can collaborate with others to review specifications
where appropriate.
• Technical understanding (data engineering). You have the detailed knowledge and
understanding of the technical concepts required for the role. You know how these fit into the wider
technical landscape.
• Testing. You can review requirements, specifications and define test conditions. You can
identify issues and risks associated with work while being able to analyse and report test activities
and results.

Tech stack:
• Azure DevOps
• Terraform
• Azure Data Factory
• Azure Databricks
• Scala
• Python
• NET Core
• MS Power BI Embedded

Skillsets required for Data Engineers: -
• SQL performance
• SQL query tuning
• SQL monitoring
• SQL Data warehousing
• SQL Indexing
• Star Schema Design


Budget: $21,000
Posted On: May 28, 2024 06:34 UTC
Category: Data Engineering
Skills:Scala, ETL, SQL, Terraform, Python, Azure DevOps, .NET Core, ETL Pipeline, Microsoft SQL Server
Skills: Scala, ETL, SQL, Terraform, Python, Azure DevOps, .NET Core, ETL Pipeline, Microsoft SQL Server
Country: India

We are seeking a Power BI Senior Specialist to act as a consultant for our Executive Dashboard project. item.title: Data Analyst - Upwork
item.description:
About the Project

We are currently building a team of individuals who will work with us to complete a Contract to Cash Audit in a series of phases. Utilizing iTel’s order data and billing data you will be responsible for the biggest lift of the project in analyzing and comparing the 2 datasets to identify discrepancies and providing that information back to other teams to review and investigate. You will also compile completed data to audit between both ordering systems. We are seeking a detail-oriented and high organized individual with previous experience in analyzing large volumes of data and creating ways to cross compare them.
These roles are crucial for ensuring the accuracy and completeness of our Contract to Cash Audit project. Each person will play a vital part in identifying discrepancies, ensuring compliance, and supporting the overall audit process.

Key Responsibilities

• Data Collection & Analysis: Collect, process, and perform a cross comparison and analyses on large datasets to extract key identified datapoints and discrepancies.
• Reporting: Prepare and maintain detailed audit templates and reports. Provide the compared data in the required format back to internal teams for review and investigation.
• Data Quality Assurance: Ensure the accuracy and integrity of data through rigorous validation and cleansing processes.
• Collaboration: Work closely with other project team members to understand their data needs and provide analytical support.
• Documentation: Maintain detailed documentation of data analysis processes and findings.
• System Alignment: Cross compare and analyze data between 2 ordering platforms and prepare data for import
Required Qualifications:
• Education: Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, or a related field.
• Experience: Minimum 3-5 years of experience in data analysis, statistical modeling or a related field.
• Technical Skills: Proficiency in data analysis and visualization tools
• Analytical Skills: Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets.
• Communication Skills: Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to present findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
• Industry Knowledge: Familiarity with the telecommunications industry is a plus.

Hourly Range: $35.00-$55.00
Posted On: May 27, 2024 18:18 UTC
Category: Data Analytics
Skills:SQL, Data Visualization, Microsoft Power BI, Microsoft Excel, Python
Skills: SQL, Data Visualization, Microsoft Power BI, Microsoft Excel, Python

item.description:
Title: Data Analyst/BI Analyst for Shopify Plus Project

Description:
We are a Shopify digital agency, seeking a skilled data analyst/BI analyst to join our team for a global client's Shopify Plus project. The ideal candidate will have experience working with large datasets, creating insightful visualizations, and providing data-driven recommendations to support business growth.

Responsibilities:

Analyze Shopify Plus store data to identify trends, patterns, and opportunities for improvement
Create dashboards, reports, and visualizations using BI tools like Tableau, Power BI, or Google Data Studio
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and provide actionable insights
Design and implement data models to support scalability and performance
Develop and maintain SQL queries to extract and manipulate data from Shopify and other data sources
Monitor key e-commerce metrics and provide regular performance updates to stakeholders
Assist in data-driven decision-making to optimize the Shopify Plus store's performance

Required Skills:

Shopify Plus: Familiarity with the Shopify Plus platform and its features
Data Analysis: Strong skills in analyzing large datasets, identifying trends, and deriving actionable insights
Business Intelligence (BI): Experience in using BI tools to create dashboards, reports, and visualizations
SQL: Proficiency in writing complex SQL queries to extract and manipulate data from databases
Data Visualization: Ability to create clear and compelling visual representations of data
E-commerce Metrics: Understanding of key e-commerce metrics and how to leverage them for growth
Statistical Analysis: Knowledge of statistical concepts and their application to real-world data
Data Modeling: Experience in designing and implementing data models to support business requirements
Python or R: Familiarity with programming languages for data manipulation, analysis, and automation
Communication Skills: Strong verbal and written communication skills to effectively present findings

Qualifications:

Experience as a data analyst or BI analyst, preferably in an e-commerce environment
Proven track record of delivering data-driven insights and recommendations
Proficiency in SQL, BI tools, and data visualization techniques
Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail
Excellent (English) communication and collaboration skills
